<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Okay.. I needed to post.. I have a few things to say.

First of all, HAHAHAHAHAHHAHAHAHHAHAHAHA this thread is funny as hell.

Second of all, HAHAHAHAHHAHAHAHHAHA okay, I'm calming down now.

Now, to my point.  It's about defective systems.  EVERY company has them, I had a defective PS2, and had to send it to the company.  When a new one (or supposedly fixed one) came back, it broke as well.

Sony was having trouble with their systems overheating as well (and my fan was not blocked).

I have also heard of many Gamecubes braking, three locally...  My friends returned them in under the 30 day store warranties (bought them from two different stores) and got their cash back..  They all waited for XBoxes and are very happy today, even though they had to spend a little extra money.

As someone else said, Microsoft is a HUGE company.  When their systems break, it is definetly going to be in the news.  Seriously, their first video game console could've had a lot more problems.

****I have also read in many places that Halo will not be on the PC, because Microsoft used their super $$$ power, and bought out the company that was making it.. And don't bitch about Microsoft buying out companies please, Sony does the same thing.****

And VH2, I'm sure all the PS2 fans are happy you only HATE a tiny part of Sony.  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/smile.gif">

ONE LAST THING, guys, don't try to argue with Tux, he pretty much knows his shit..  Not to mention he also helps out a lot with EQ stuff.


